tion_Party\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the next candidate\", \"from\": 1108, \"to\": 1126}, {\"ngram\": \"prime minister\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1145}, {\"ngram\": \"turn\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1164}, {\"ngram\": \"a government\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1187}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After several failed attempts, the leftwing coalition agreed on a name:Castets, a 37-year-old senior civil servant who has worked at the general directorate of the treasury and the French anti-money-laundering authority.\", \"from\": 1189, \"to\": 1409, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1370, \"end\": 1376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9997245830787507, \"rank\": 0.00021359558267393736, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"several failed attempts\", \"from\": 1195, \"to\": 1218}, {\"ngram\": \"the leftwing coalition\", \"from\": 1220, \"to\": 1242}, {\"ngram\": \"a name\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1259}, {\"ngram\": \"Castets\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1267}, {\"ngram\": \"a 37-year-old senior civil servant\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1303}, {\"ngram\": \"the general directorate\", \"from\": 1322, \"to\": 1345}, {\"ngram\": \"the treasury\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1361}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has alreadysaidshe is willing to compromise with all parties (except the far right) - a necessity if legislation is to be passed, given the NFP's narrow win.\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1571, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1554, \"end\": 1557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 5.364683160247197e-12, \"text\": \"NFP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"alreadysaidshe\", \"from\": 1418, \"to\": 1432}, {\"ngram\": \"all parties\", \"from\": 1463, \"to\": 1474}, {\"ngram\": \"the far right\", \"from\": 1483, \"to\": 1496}, {\"ngram\": \"a necessity\", \"from\": 1500, \"to\": 1511}, {\"ngram\": \"legislation\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1526}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Macron hasrefused to ask herto take up a position as prime minister, and has said he will not name a new one before the end of the Paris 2024 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1573, \"to\": 1733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1577, \"end\": 1583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9703456552891767e-42, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"herto\", \"from\": 1602, \"to\": 1607}, {\"ngram\": \"a position\", \"from\": 1616, \"to\": 1626}, {\"ngram\": \"prime minister\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1644}, {\"ngram\": \"a new one\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1685}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 1693, \"to\": 1700}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris 2024 Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1704, \"to\": 1732}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With the Paralympics ending on 8 September, that's almost six more weeks of political limbo.\", \"from\": 1734, \"to\": 1826, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Paralympics\", \"from\": 1739, \"to\": 1754}, {\"ngram\": \"8 September\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1776}, {\"ngram\": \"almost six more weeks\", \"from\": 1785, \"to\": 1806}, {\"ngram\": \"political limbo\", \"from\": 1810, \"to\": 1825}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In truth, no one knows when Macron will deign to name someone: he revels in being in full control of the agenda.\", \"from\": 1827, \"to\": 1939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1855, \"end\": 1861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9703456552891767e-42, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"truth\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1835}, {\"ngram\": \"no one\", \"from\": 1837, \"to\": 1843}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 1881, \"to\": 1888}, {\"ngram\": \"full control\", \"from\": 1912, \"to\": 1924}, {\"ngram\": \"the agenda\", \"from\": 1928, \"to\": 1938}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The constitution states that \\\"the president names the prime minister\\\".\", \"from\": 1940, \"to\": 2010, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The constitution\", \"from\": 1940, \"to\": 1956}, {\"ngram\": \"the president\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 1983}, {\"ngram\": \"the prime minister\", \"from\": 1990, \"to\": 2008}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It does not stipulate that the PM must be chosen from the largest parliamentary bloc, although when he found himself in this pickle, President Fran\\u00e7ois Mitterrandsaidhe would \\\"naturally align his choice with the will of the people\\\".\", \"from\": 2011, \"to\": 2243, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the PM\", \"from\": 2038, \"to\": 2044}, {\"ngram\": \"the largest parliamentary bloc\", \"from\": 2065, \"to\": 2095}, {\"ngram\": \"this pickle\", \"from\": 2131, \"to\": 2142}, {\"ngram\": \"President Fran\\u00e7ois Mitterrandsaidhe\", \"from\": 2144, \"to\": 2179}, {\"ngram\": \"his choice\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2213}, {\"ngram\": \"the people\", \"from\": 2231, \"to\": 2241}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The risk, otherwise, is to lose a vote of no confidence in the premiership.\", \"from\": 2244, \"to\": 2319, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The risk\", \"from\": 2244, \"to\": 2252}, {\"ngram\": \"a vote\", \"from\": 2276, \"to\": 2282}, {\"ngram\": \"no confidence\", \"from\": 2286, \"to\": 2299}, {\"ngram\": \"the premiership\", \"from\": 2303, \"to\": 2318}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And so the decision can only be made by Macron- making him \\\"the master of the clocks\\\" as he somewhat pompously likes to call himself.\", \"from\": 2320, \"to\": 2453, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the decision\", \"from\": 2327, \"to\": 2339}, {\"ngram\": \"the clocks\", \"from\": 2394, \"to\": 2404}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His logic for delaying - at least in his public statements - is a little confused.\", \"from\": 2455, \"to\": 2537, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His logic\", \"from\": 2455, \"to\": 2464}, {\"ngram\": \"delaying\", \"from\": 2469, \"to\": 2477}, {\"ngram\": \"his public statements\", \"from\": 2492, \"to\": 2513}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking to public broadcasterFrance2, he said that \\\"the issue is not whether we have a name, but whether we can have a majority at the Assembly, so that a government can pass reforms and a budget, and move the country forward\\\".\", \"from\": 2538, \"to\": 2766, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2674, \"end\": 2682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deliberative_assembly\", \"score\": 0.9999808455883824, \"rank\": 1.848521812270832e-05, \"text\": \"Assembly\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deliberative_assembly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deliberative_assembly\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the issue\", \"from\": 2591, \"to\": 2600}, {\"ngram\": \"a name\", \"from\": 2624, \"to\": 2630}, {\"ngram\": \"a majority\", \"from\": 2656, \"to\": 2666}, {\"ngram\": \"a government\", \"from\": 2692, \"to\": 2704}, {\"ngram\": \"reforms\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2721}, {\"ngram\": \"a budget\", \"from\": 2726, \"to\": 2734}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 2745, \"to\": 2756}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Usually, however, naming a new prime minister is the first step towards a majority.\", \"from\": 2767, \"to\": 2850, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a new prime minister\", \"from\": 2792, \"to\": 2812}, {\"ngram\": \"the first step\", \"from\": 2816, \"to\": 2830}, {\"ngram\": \"a majority\", \"from\": 2839, \"to\": 2849}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once chosen, the new PM has the political authority to begin forming alliances to vote on reforms and budgets, and thus attempt to govern.\", \"from\": 2851, \"to\": 2989, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the new PM\", \"from\": 2864, \"to\": 2874}, {\"ngram\": \"the political authority\", \"from\": 2879, \"to\": 2902}, {\"ngram\": \"alliances\", \"from\": 2920, \"to\": 2929}, {\"ngram\": \"reforms\", \"from\": 2941, \"to\": 2948}, {\"ngram\": \"budgets\", \"from\": 2953, \"to\": 2960}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But what does the president really seek to achieve in dragging his feet?\", \"from\": 2991, \"to\": 3063, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the president\", \"from\": 3005, \"to\": 3018}, {\"ngram\": \"his feet\", \"from\": 3054, \"to\": 3062}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By putting French politics on pause for a duration of his choosing, Macron hopes for the leftwing alliance to deteriorate enough for the situation to turn in his favour.\", \"from\": 3064, \"to\": 3233, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3075, \"end\": 3081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9997245830787507, \"rank\": 0.00021359558267393736, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 3132, \"end\": 3138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9703456552891767e-42, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"pause\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3099}, {\"ngram\": \"a duration\", \"from\": 3104, \"to\": 3114}, {\"ngram\": \"his choosing\", \"from\": 3118, \"to\": 3130}, {\"ngram\": \"the leftwing alliance\", \"from\": 3149, \"to\": 3170}, {\"ngram\": \"the situation\", \"from\": 3197, \"to\": 3210}, {\"ngram\": \"his favour\", \"from\": 3222, \"to\": 3232}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His theory: the French want an \\\"Olympics truce\\\" and to forget, for a time, about politics.\", \"from\": 3234, \"to\": 3324, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3250, \"end\": 3256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9997245830787507, \"rank\": 0.00021359558267393736, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His theory\", \"from\": 3234, \"to\": 3244}, {\"ngram\": \"an \\\"Olympics truce\", \"from\": 3262, \"to\": 3280}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 3301, \"to\": 3307}, {\"ngram\": \"politics\", \"from\": 3315, \"to\": 3323}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not impossible that the left could implode in this period: the longer Macron waits, the more time for this alliance of wildly diverse parties to shatter over policy differences.\", \"from\": 3325, \"to\": 3507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3400, \"end\": 3406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9703456552891767e-42, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the left\", \"from\": 3350, \"to\": 3358}, {\"ngram\": \"this period\", \"from\": 3376, \"to\": 3387}, {\"ngram\": \"the more time\", \"from\": 3414, \"to\": 3427}, {\"ngram\": \"this alliance\", \"from\": 3432, \"to\": 3445}, {\"ngram\": \"wildly diverse parties\", \"from\": 3449, \"to\": 3471}, {\"ngram\": \"policy differences\", \"from\": 3488, \"to\": 3506}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet they have a common programme - Macron's party and its potential allies, the rightwing R\\u00e9publicains, can not say as much.\", \"from\": 3509, \"to\": 3633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3544, \"end\": 3550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9703456552891767e-42, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a common programme\", \"from\": 3523, \"to\": 3541}, {\"ngram\": \"its potential allies\", \"from\": 3563, \"to\": 3583}, {\"ngram\": \"the rightwing R\\u00e9publicains\", \"from\": 3585, \"to\": 3611}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In truth, this is the last ditch gamble of a president running out of road - and he has no one to blame for his desperate position but himself.\", \"from\": 3634, \"to\": 3777, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"truth\", \"from\": 3637, \"to\": 3642}, {\"ngram\": \"the last ditch gamble\", \"from\": 3652, \"to\": 3673}, {\"ngram\": \"a president\", \"from\": 3677, \"to\": 3688}, {\"ngram\": \"road\", \"from\": 3704, \"to\": 3708}, {\"ngram\": \"no one\", \"from\": 3722, \"to\": 3728}, {\"ngram\": \"his desperate position\", \"from\": 3742, \"to\": 3764}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After calling a snap parliamentary election in response to the far-right surging in the disastrous European election results, his party lost 76 seats, cratering its already shaky majority.\", \"from\": 3778, \"to\": 3966, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a snap parliamentary election\", \"from\": 3792, \"to\": 3821}, {\"ngram\": \"response\", \"from\": 3825, \"to\": 3833}, {\"ngram\": \"the far-right surging\", \"from\": 3837, \"to\": 3858}, {